    journeyNarrative:"This itinerary is built for travelers who already know they want depth over breadth — those who have read about Axum's stelae or seen a photograph of a church clinging to a Tigray cliff face and decided that one region, understood properly, matters more than a broader but shallower circuit. It skips Lalibela and Gondar entirely, not because they aren't remarkable, but because eight days spent entirely in Ethiopia's oldest religious landscape lets you go further into the history, the geology, and the genuine physical challenge of reaching these sites than a itinerary trying to cover the whole north ever could. It suits travelers in decent physical condition, comfortable with a real climb, who want specialist depth rather than a highlights reel.",
