      "The Blue Nile Falls stop is placed as a mid-route excursion during the drive south, rather than a dedicated day, since the walk itself is short and works naturally alongside a travel day.",
      "Lake Tana is given a full, unhurried day at the end of the route, timed as a calm close after Gondar's denser castle-and-church days.",
      "No overland long-haul driving is required — the only road day is the moderate Gondar-to-Bahir Dar transfer, keeping the whole itinerary genuinely easy-paced as advertised.",
