    journeyNarrative:"This route exists for photographers who want to work seriously, not just point a camera out of a moving vehicle. Every community stop is scheduled around actual light — early morning and late afternoon — and each major community gets two consecutive days rather than one, because the second visit is reliably where the real images and real trust both appear. The consent-based practice underpinning this trip isn't a compliance checkbox; it's the reason communities keep agreeing to work with Sawla's photography groups at all, and it produces better pictures than a rushed, uneasy encounter ever could.",
