    journeyNarrative:"This itinerary is built for travelers who want to earn their wildlife encounters on foot rather than from a vehicle window — the Simien escarpment rewards walkers specifically, since gelada troops, Walia ibex, and lammergeiers are all best experienced at the unhurried pace and close range that trekking allows. It suits genuinely active travelers comfortable with multiple consecutive days of high-altitude walking and basic camp conditions, in exchange for a depth of encounter that a shorter, vehicle-based visit cannot match.",
